# =============================================================================
# polykey — Matrix AI's "Polykey CLI - Open Source
#           Decentralized Secret Sharing System for Zero
#           Trust Workflows" — a TypeScript-Node CLI for
#           Polykey, a peer-to-peer secret-sharing and
#           identity-management system based on the libp2p
#           networking stack.  Provides per-host "vaults"
#           that store secrets (API keys, certificates,
#           passwords, files) and exchange them with other
#           authenticated Polykey nodes over an encrypted
#           P2P mesh — without any central server.
#           Distinguishing from Vault (HashiCorp), 1Password,
#           Bitwarden, gopass, age, and other secret-management
#           tools by:
#             - DECENTRALIZED P2P — no central server, no
#               cloud-hosted vault; secrets shared directly
#               between authenticated Polykey nodes over
#               libp2p.  Eliminates single-vendor risk +
#               eliminates network-attached-vault-as-single-
#               point-of-failure.
#             - ZERO-TRUST WORKFLOWS — each Polykey vault
#               is a sandbox with its own identity (cryptographic
#               key); inter-vault sharing requires explicit
#               per-secret + per-recipient authorization
#             - 9 COMMAND GROUPS via commander:
#                 * agent          — agent (background daemon)
#                                    management (start / stop /
#                                    lock / unlock / status)
#                 * audit          — audit log inspection
#                 * auth           — authentication (login /
#                                    logout / token mgmt)
#                 * bootstrap      — initialize new Polykey
#                                    node
#                 * identities     — external-identity linking
#                                    (GitHub, GitLab, etc.)
#                 * keys           — keypair management
#                                    (generate / encrypt /
#                                    decrypt / sign / verify)
#                 * nodes          — peer node mgmt (add /
#                                    remove / connect / claim)
#                 * notifications  — inter-node messaging
#                                    (send / read / inbox)
#                 * secrets        — secret CRUD (create /
#                                    read / update / delete /
#                                    list / share)
#                 * vaults         — vault mgmt (create /
#                                    delete / clone / pull /
#                                    push / list / share)
#             - libp2p P2P NETWORKING — built on libp2p's
#               modular P2P stack (transports: TCP / WebSocket /
#               QUIC; multiplexing: yamux; encryption: noise /
#               TLS); same protocol family used by IPFS +
#               Filecoin + Ethereum's portal network
#             - GIT-LIKE VAULT MODEL — vaults are content-
#               addressed git repositories under the hood;
#               support clone / pull / push / merge between
#               peer nodes
#             - DUAL BINARY NAMES — `polykey` (full) +
#               `pk` (short alias), both pointing to the same
#               dist/polykey.mjs entry
#             - JSON / TEXT OUTPUT — --format json or default
#               text; structured output for scripting
#             - VERBOSE LEVELS via -v / -vv / -vvv — increasing
#               log verbosity (info / debug / silly)
#             - NODE PATH via --node-path — directory where
#               this Polykey instance stores its state
#               (default ~/.local/share/polykey on Linux,
#               equivalent paths on macOS/Windows)
#             - PASSWORD FILE via --password-file — read
#               vault unlock password from file (avoids
#               passing on CLI)
#             - AJV SCHEMA VALIDATION — JSON Schema
#               validation throughout the codebase for
#               messages exchanged between Polykey nodes,
#               configuration files, and external API
#               responses; ensures wire-format compatibility
#               across versions
#             - @matrixai/logger STRUCTURED LOGGING —
#               structured logging with per-handler
#               formatters (JSON for machine-readable,
#               formatted for terminal)
#             - WORKER THREADS via threads.js — heavy crypto
#               operations (key generation, encryption,
#               signing) offloaded to worker threads to keep
#               the agent responsive
#             - EXIT HANDLERS — graceful shutdown hooks for
#               SIGINT / SIGTERM that propagate to the
#               PolykeyAgent + worker manager
#           Used by: DevSecOps teams implementing zero-trust
#           secret-sharing across multiple environments,
#           home-lab + small-business users wanting
